snippet.textDisplay:
In my unprofessional and inconsequential opinion: 
The Track:
Sounds like a Bay inspired piece I could easily see E-40 featuring on, maybe even Mac Dre (G.R.H.S). I could see this being a track that was made for fun to get his name out. However, as an attention grabbing piece Koala is underwhelming. I think this could've faired better if, in Simon Dominic fashion, this was a collaborative piece with many different rappers.

Audience:
I am curious to know who the targeted audience listed in his business proposal is. International kpop fans? Rap and hip-hop fans? Koreans? The west? Throw some darts see where they land?

Lyrics:
Misplaced concepts on Koala's part but then again who is your audience, sir? No rememberable bars for me until Jessi comes.

Video Concept:
The subject and video clash. They mixed bubblegum kpop glam with street glam like oil and water. 
They could've easily handled this with 1 or 2 sets. Put one of the friends as a bouncer like it's a private tailgate and if they used the pink room it shouldve been designated for Jessi, using the method of someone watching it from their phone and pushing into the scene.

Jessi:
 It really could've been titled Jessi ft Koala and no one would be wiser. She carried the song, the music video, everything. Pay that back with a fullness Koala bear.
